{{nihongo|'''Tsunashima Ryōsen'''|綱島 梁川|Tsunashima Ryōsen|May 27, 1873–September 14, 1907}} was a [[Japanese author]] and philosopher. He was a graduate of [[Tōkyō Senmon Gakkō]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Milton in Japan, 1871-1971 |last=Miyanishi |first=Mitsuo |year=1975 |publisher=Kinseido |page=68 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Sx88AAAAIAAJ&q=%22Ryosen+Tsunashima%22&dq=%22Ryosen+Tsunashima%22&num=100&pgis=1 }}</ref> He was originally a [[rationalist]] and then became a [[Christian]].<ref>{{cite book |title=History of Japanese Religion |last=Anesaki |first=Masaharu |year=1930 |publisher=K. Paul, Trench, Trubner & Co., ltd. |page=381 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Pe4dAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Ryosen+Tsunashima%22&dq=%22Ryosen+Tsunashima%22&num=100&pgis=1 }}</ref> He is buried in Tokyo's [[Zōshigaya cemetery]].<ref>[https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/6134112 Find-a-grave entry]</ref>

