[[File:Wincenty Lutoslawski 1909.jpg|thumb|Portrait of Wincenty Lutosławski by [[Olga Boznańska]] (1909)]] '''Wincenty Lutosławski''' (1863–1954) was a Polish philosopher, author, and member of the [[Polish National League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cejsh.icm.edu.pl/cejsh/cgi-bin/getdoc.cgi?05PLAAAA00411003 |title=CEJSH Publishing Information}}</ref> He is well known for coining the term "[[stylometry]]".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.benjamins.com/cgi-bin/t_articles.cgi?bookid=HL%2031%3A2%2F3&artid=167056172 |title=John Benjamins: Wincenty Lutosławski}}</ref> A multilingual [[philosophy|philosopher]] who used literary analysis to establish the chronology of [[Plato]]'s writings. Married to the Spanish poet [[Sofía Casanova]], then divorced. Half-brother of Józef Lutosławski, father of the composer [[Witold Lutosławski]].
== Works == * ''Principes de stylométrie'' (1890) * ''O logice Platona'' (I–II, Kraków 1891–1892, I: O tradycyi tekstu Platona, II: Dotychczasowe poglądy na logikę Platona i zadania dalszych badań nad tym przedmiotem) * ''O pierwszych trzech tetralogiach dzieł Platona'' (Kraków 1896) * ''The Origin and Growth of Plato’s Logic. With an Account of Plato’s Style and of the Chronology of His Writings'' (1897) * ''Platon jako twórca idealizmu'' (Warsaw 1899) * ''Źródła pesymizmu'' (Kraków 1899) * ''Z dziedziny myśli. Studja filozoficzne.'' 1888–1899 (Kraków 1900) * ''Wykłady Jagiellońskie'' (I–II, Kraków 1901–1902) * ''The Polish Nation'' (Berlin 1908) * ''[[Gdańsk and East Prussia]]'' (1919) * ''Lithuania and White Ruthenia'' (1919) * ''The Ruthenian Question in Galicia'' (1919) * ''Bolshevism and Poland'' (1919) * ''The World of Souls'' (1924) * ''The Knowledge of Reality'' (1930) * ''Pre-existence and Reincarnation'' (1928)
